{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Act|6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","chapter":6,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:6:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":6,"verse":1,"text":"In those days, as the disciples were increasing in number, there arose a complaint by the Hellenistic Jews against the Hebraic Jews that their widows were being overlooked in the daily distribution.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:6:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":6,"verse":2,"text":"The Twelve summoned the whole company of the disciples and said, “It would not be right for us to give up preaching the word of God to wait on tables.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:6:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":6,"verse":3,"text":"Brothers and sisters, select from among you seven men of good reputation, full of the Spirit and wisdom, whom we can appoint to this duty.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:6:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":6,"verse":4,"text":"But we will devote ourselves to prayer and to the ministry of the word.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:6:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":6,"verse":5,"text":"This proposal pleased the whole company. So they chose Stephen, a man full of faith and the Holy Spirit, and Philip, Prochorus, Nicanor, Timon, Parmenas, and Nicolaus, a convert from Antioch.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:6:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":6,"verse":6,"text":"They had them stand before the apostles, who prayed and laid their hands on them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:6:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":6,"verse":7,"text":"So the word of God spread, the disciples in Jerusalem increased greatly in number, and a large group of priests became obedient to the faith.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:6:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":6,"verse":8,"text":"Now Stephen, full of grace and power, was performing great wonders and signs among the people.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:6:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":6,"verse":9,"text":"Opposition arose, however, from some members of the Freedmen’s Synagogue, composed of both Cyrenians and Alexandrians, and some from Cilicia and Asia, and they began to argue with Stephen.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:6:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":6,"verse":10,"text":"But they were unable to stand up against his wisdom and the Spirit by whom he was speaking.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:6:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":6,"verse":11,"text":"Then they secretly persuaded some men to say, “We heard him speaking blasphemous words against Moses and God.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:6:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":6,"verse":12,"text":"They stirred up the people, the elders, and the scribes; so they came, seized him, and took him to the Sanhedrin.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:6:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":6,"verse":13,"text":"They also presented false witnesses who said, “This man never stops speaking against this holy place and the law.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:6:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":6,"verse":14,"text":"For we heard him say that this Jesus of Nazareth will destroy this place and change the customs that Moses handed down to us.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:6:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":6,"verse":15,"text":"And all who were sitting in the Sanhedrin looked intently at him and saw that his face was like the face of an angel.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","chapter":6,"paragraphStarts":[1,7,8,11],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Seven Chosen to Serve"},{"beforeVerse":8,"text":"Stephen Accused of Blasphemy"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:6:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"In those days, as the disciples "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 9:10","book":"Mat","chapter":9,"verse":10,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 10:10","book":"Mrk","chapter":10,"verse":10,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 6:1","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":1,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 6:3","book":"Jhn","chapter":6,"verse":3,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 9:1","book":"Act","chapter":9,"verse":1,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 9:10","book":"Act","chapter":9,"verse":10,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 9:19","book":"Act","chapter":9,"verse":19,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 9:25","book":"Act","chapter":9,"verse":25,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 21:4","book":"Act","chapter":21,"verse":4,"letter":"i"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 21:16","book":"Act","chapter":21,"verse":16,"letter":"j"},{"kind":"text","text":" were increasing in number, there aros